LEETCODE 215. Kth Largest Element in an Array
Given an integer array nums and an integer k, return the kth largest element in the array.
Note that it is the kth largest element in the sorted order, not the kth distinct element.
Can you solve it without sorting?

Example 1:
Input: nums = [3,2,1,5,6,4], k = 2
Output: 5

Example 2:
Input: nums = [3,2,3,1,2,4,5,5,6], k = 4
Output: 4
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

BRUTE FORCE CODE: TIME COMPLEXITY:O(N LOGN) SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(N)

Algorithm Steps:
1️⃣ Create a Max-Heap (PriorityQueue with descending order)
2️⃣ Insert all N numbers into heap
3️⃣ Remove (poll) K-1 times
4️⃣ The next polled element is the Kth largest

BRUTE FORCE CODE:
class Pair{ 
    private int kee;
    Pair(int key)
    {
        this.kee=key;
    }
    public int getKee(){
        return kee;
    }
}
class Solution {
    public int findKthLargest(int[] nums, int k) {
        PriorityQueue<Pair> pq=new PriorityQueue<>((a,b) -> b.getKee() - a.getKee());
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++)
        {
            pq.add(new Pair(nums[i]));
        }
        for(int i=0;i<=k-2;i++)
        {
            pq.poll();
        }
        Pair result=pq.poll();
        return result.getKee();
    }
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
OPTIMAL CODE: TIME COMPLEXITY:O(N LOGK) SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(K)

Algorithm Steps:
1️⃣ Create a Min-Heap
2️⃣ For each number in array
  • Add to heap
  • If heap size > K → remove smallest
3️⃣ After loop, heap.peek() is the answer

OPTIMAL CODE:
class Solution {
    public int findKthLargest(int[] nums, int k) {
        PriorityQueue<Integer> pq=new PriorityQueue<>();
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++)
        {
            pq.add(nums[i]);
            if(pq.size()>k)
            {
                pq.poll();
            }
        }
        
        return pq.poll();
    }
}
